---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---

<BaseLayout title="Security Policy | Gold Shore" description="Security disclosure and vulnerability reporting policy.">
  <section class="gs-section gs-section--padded">
    <div class="gs-container" style="max-width: 800px;">
      <h1>Security Policy</h1>
      <p>
        Gold Shore welcomes responsible vulnerability disclosures that help protect our systems,
        partners, and users.
      </p>

      <h2>Safe Harbor</h2>
      <p>
        If you act in good faith, avoid privacy violations and service disruption, and follow this policy,
        we will not initiate legal action against you for your research.
      </p>

      <h2>Out of Scope</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Third-party services and SaaS providers not operated by Gold Shore</li>
        <li>Social engineering, phishing, or physical attacks</li>
        <li>Denial-of-service or volumetric testing</li>
        <li>Automated scans that materially degrade service availability</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Response Timeline</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Initial acknowledgment target: within 3 business days</li>
        <li>Triage and severity assessment target: within 7 business days</li>
        <li>Status updates: at least every 14 days for in-progress reports</li>
      </ul>



      <h2>JWT Secret Management (JWTHS256KEY)</h2>
      <p>
        For HS256 signing, use a high-entropy secret with at least 32 bytes (256 bits).
        Generate it locally and store it only as a Worker secret.
      </p>
      <pre><code>node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('base64url'))"</code></pre>
      <p>
        Bind the generated value to Cloudflare Workers with:
      </p>
      <pre><code>wrangler secret put JWTHS256KEY</code></pre>
      <p>
        Never commit JWT secrets in source control or plain-text configuration files.
      </p>

      <h2>Credential Rotation</h2>
      <p>
        If any API keys or personal access tokens are exposed in prompts, logs, screenshots,
        or commits, treat them as compromised and rotate them immediately.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Revoke and regenerate exposed GitHub personal access tokens.</li>
        <li>Rotate Cloudflare API tokens and service credentials.</li>
        <li>Update dependent systems and confirm least-privilege scopes.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to Report</h2>
      <p>
        Send reports to <a href="mailto:security@goldshore.ai">security@goldshore.ai</a> and include
        reproduction steps, affected endpoints, and any proof-of-concept details needed for validation.
      </p>

      <p>
        For machine-readable policy details, see
        <a href="/.well-known/security.txt">/.well-known/security.txt</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
